    "Therefore, there is a need for a benchmarking study to systematically evaluate the impact of threshold selections on the performance of GNN models.",
    "Page 31 of 38 49 Thresholding strategies have a direct impact on class imbalance.",
    "For example, one can designate the upper quartile and lower quartile scores as synergistic and antagonistic, respectively, in order to attain a balanced dataset and improve the accuracy of categorization (i.e., reduce the risk of false positive or false negative annotations resulting from more relaxed thresholding).",
    "However, this approach comes at the cost of reducing the size of the training set.",
    "Alternatively, techniques like oversampling or undersampling, such as SMOTE (Chawla et al. 2002), can be employed to balance the dataset."
